definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + L-glutamate + factor F420-0 -eq- GDP + H+ + factor gamma-F420-1 + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + L-glutamate + factor gamma-F420-1 -eq- GDP + H+ + factor gamma-F420-2 + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + thymine + acceptor -eq- 5-methyl-barbiturate + donor-H2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 GTP -eq- cyclic di-3',5'-guanylate + 2 diphosphate + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  delta(2)-isopentenyl diphosphate + ATP -eq- diphosphate + N6-(delta(2)-isopentenyl)adenosine 5'-triphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  delta2-isopentenyl diphosphate + ADP -eq- diphosphate + N6-(delta(2)-isopentenyl)adenosine 5'-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  demethylphylloquinone + S-adenosyl-L-methionine -eq- phylloquinone + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-aminobenzoate + ATP + amino acid -eq- 4-aminobenzoyl amino acid conjugate + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoate + ATP + amino acid -eq- benzoyl amino acid conjugate + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  vanillate + ATP + amino acid -eq- vanillate amino acid conjugate + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxybenzoate + ATP + amino acid -eq- 4-hydroxybenzoyl amino acid conjugate + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate + H2O -eq- a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate + phosphate + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UTP + N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine 1-phosphate -eq- diphosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine.

Catalysis of the formation of a double bond between C8 and C9 of the long chain base of a sphingolipid. For example, sphinganine (d18 - 0) -eq- 8-sphingenine (d18 - 1delta8) -  phytosphinganine (t18 - 0) -eq- 8-phytosphingenine (t18 - 1delta8) -  and 4-sphingenine (18 - 1delta4) -eq- 4,8-sphingadienine (d18 - 2delta4,8).
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-aconitate + H2O -eq- isocitrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a C-19 gibberellin + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- a C-19 2-beta-hydroxygibberellin + succinate + CO2. C-19 gibberellin refers to a gibberellin with nineteen carbons.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a C-20 gibberellin + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- a C-20 2-beta-hydroxygibberellin + succinate + CO2. C-20 gibberellin refers to a gibberellin with twenty carbons.
Catalysis of the transfer of a pentosyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

Catalysis of the reaction -  1-18 - 3-3-16 - 0-phosphatidylglycerol -eq- 1-18 - 3-3-trans-16 - 1-phosphatidylglycerol + 2 H+. This reaction is the formation of a trans double bond between carbon 3 and carbon 4 (counting from the carboxyl end) of palmitic acid, which is specifically esterified to the sn-2 glyceryl carbon of phosphatidylglycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-butyrate + UDP-D-glucose -eq- indole-3-butyryl-beta-1-D-glucose + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  salicylic acid + UDP-glucose -eq- salicylic acid glucose ester + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  salicylic acid + UDP-glucose -eq- salicylic acid 2-O-glucoside + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoic acid + UDP-glucose -eq- benzoic acid glucose ester + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lysophosphatidic acid + H2O -eq- phosphate + monoacylglycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  all-trans-retinol + NADP+ -eq- all-trans-retinal + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + L-leucine -eq- 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + L-glutamatic acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + L-valine -eq- 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoic acid + L-glutamatic acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + L-isoleucine -eq- (S)-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoic acid + L-glutamic acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GMP + diphosphate -eq- guanine + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1D-myo-inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 1,4-bisphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate + H2O -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4-trisphosphate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-propane-1,2-diol + NAD+ -eq- (R)-lactaldehyde + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-propane-1,2-diol + NAD+ -eq- (S)-lactaldehyde + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  zeaxanthin + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 -eq- antheraxanthin + NAD(P)+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  antheraxanthin + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 -eq- all-trans-violaxanthin + NAD(P)+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nitroalkane + H2O + O2 -eq- an aldehyde or ketone + nitrite + H2O2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing 2'-O-methyluracil.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing 2'-O-methylcytosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-methylethanolamine phosphate + S-adenosyl-L-methionine -eq- N,N-dimethylethanolamine phosphate + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  farnesol + nucleoside triphosphate -eq- farnesyl monophosphate + nucleoside diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-trans,-6-trans-farnesol + CTP -eq- 2-trans,-6-trans-farnesyl monophosphate + CDP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  geraniol + nucleoside triphosphate -eq- geranyl monophosphate + nucleoside diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  geranylgeraniol + nucleoside triphosphate -eq- all-trans-geranyl-geranyl monophosphate + nucleoside diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  geranylgeraniol + CTP -eq- all-trans-geranyl-geranyl monophosphate + CDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  prenol + nucleoside triphosphate -eq- prenyl phosphate + nucleoside diphosphate activity.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ent-copalyl diphosphate -eq- ent-pimara-9(11),15-diene + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methylbutanol + NADP+ -eq- 3-methylbutanal + NADPH + H+. 3-methylbutanal is also known as isovaleraldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methylbutanol + NAD+ -eq- 3-methylbutanal + NADH + H+. 3-methylbutanal is also known as isovaleraldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-arabinitol + NADP+ -eq- D-xylulose + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (+)-copalyl diphosphate -eq- abieta-8(14),12-diene + diphosphate.
